I’m always looking for last minute easy diy projects to gift and i love these oven mitts! A pair comes together in about an hour and I used materials from my scrap stash. The pattern itself is *free* from @bombazine 🎄 
-
Tips: 
- use wool coating scraps or multiple layers of batting to get adequate insulation
- cut the lining slightly smaller than the outer fabric to reduce the bagging inside the mitt
- use fun decorative stitches for quilting! It makes the final product feel like they took more time than they did 😉
-
Let me know what other fun and easy holiday DIY gift ideas you all have!
-

Had a craving last night for the sweet and salty Filipino spaghetti 🍝! Suuuch a nostalgic flavor for me and so so freakin good 😋
-
Ingredients:
Bucatini
1 lb ground pork
Sliced hot dogs 🌭 
Minced garlic
Sliced onion
Diced red peppers
Finely chopped carrots 🥕 
1lb 8oz tomato sauce 
10oz tomato paste 
Condensed milk to taste ~4oz
Fish sauce and salt to taste
Shredded sharp cheddar
-
1. Sauté garlic and onion
2. Add ground pork, brown
3. Add peppers and carrots, followed by hot dogs, add 1 cup water and simmer
4. Add tomato sauce and paste
5. Add condensed milk, simmer 
6. Add salt and fish sauce to taste
7. While sauce is simmering, boil pasta according to package instructions
8. Combine sauce and pasta, top with cheddar!
-

Hey hi hello!!!! 👋🏽 With my new haircut, I figure it’s time for a reintroduction 🤗 

I’m Danica! I’m based out of Houston, TX. Most days you’ll find me at the hospital - I’m a few months away from finishing my OB/GYN residency 🎉 I love delivering babies, gynecologic surgeries, and advocating for women’s health 💪🏽 

I’ve always had a passion for DIY since I was in pre-school and my teachers told my mom that I was always messing with the scissors ✂️ I picked up knitting in middle school, dabbled in crochet in college, and sewed my first quilt the summer before starting medical school.

I made my first dress in the fall of 2017, which seems so long ago now!! I could not get the idea of a flannel plaid shift dress out of my head, and I couldn’t find one in stores, so I bought fabric and found a great YouTube tutorial online and went to work! Needless to say, it was a disaster and it took me dayssss. Admittedly it was bold of me to think I could install a zipper, inset sleeves, and add a facing for my first attempt 😂 from then, I was hooked!

I started this Instagram in the fall of 2018 when I was in the 4th year of medical school, after a whole year of following many sewing accounts. I never imagined that it would take off or I’d become an ~influencer~ 🤣

Fast forward a little over four years later and I’m so grateful for the small community I’ve grown here on the ‘gram! 

While residency has made it nearly impossible to keep up with regular posts and projects, I’m hoping to post more, share more of my everyday antics! This year, I plan to share more home DIYs, more clothes of course, and hopefully more cooking and travel content! ✈️ 

Last but not least, thank you to all of you for the love, inspiration, and laughs! This Instagram is my little escape and much needed creative outlet, and I am so glad to be here 🥰 Say hi down below! Also please share what you’d like to see from me! 

———-

You’ve got a *pizza* my heart! 🍕

Pizza sauce recipe:
1. Over medium heat, bring one can crushed San marzano tomatoes, 2 tbsp olive oil, 6 crushed cloves of garlic to a simmer
2. Stir periodically, simmer at low to medium low heat until desired consistency (~15-20 minutes)
3. Salt to taste!

The best food we ate in Oahu:

1. Mai Tais at the Royal Hawaiian 🌺 it was packed and crazy for golden hour but we snagged seats at the bar and watched the sunset. Picture perfect and totally worth the crowd and the hassle. @royal_hawaiian 
2. Açaí bowl at Island Vintage Coffee. It’s located in a super touristy part of Waikiki but I honestly have not found a better açaí bowl. I dream of these bowls and it’s an absolute must-stop whenever I’m in Hawai’i! The honey is to die for and the fruit is so fresh. @islandvintagecoffee 
3. Foodland Poké - I will stand by saying that foodland has the best poke. The free-standing spots you’ll find on yelp etc are great of course but foodland is truly the bread and butter of poke in Hawai’i and is so consistently amazing that you cannot go wrong. I got the California roll ahi and the Hawaiian style ahi on white rice and it was sooooo freaking good. The fish is fresh, perfectly seasoned, and you can’t beat the price. @foodlandhi 
4. Banana pancakes with macadamia nut sauce at Boots and Kimos in Kailua. This was the perfect post hike meal and the sauce was SO good. Perfectly nutty, creamy, and the pancakes were just the right amount of fluffy and buttery. 
5. Garlic shrimp from Big Wave Shrimp Truck on the North Shore. This was surprisingly better than I thought! I’ve never had the garlic shrimp from the north shore before and I had pretty low expectations but this dish is exactly as described. Super buttery, garlicky, and the shrimp is cooked perfectly. This truck also adds on a slice of pineapple for the perfect bite! Definitely recommend. @bigwaveshrimp 
6. Hapa Açaí Bowl from Haleiwa Bowls. This is one of the most commonly recommended açaí bowl spots on YouTube and it was also fantastic! Loved the coconut flakes and the quality of the granola and fruit was great. Perfect after a long day in the north shore 🌊 @haleiwabowls 
7. Matsumoto Shave Ice. This was also a bucket list spot for me! It was a solid shave ice - I got lilikoi, guava, and pineapple. I prefer Waiola shave ice 🍧 but I can see why people love this spot so much! @matsumotoshaveice 

#hawaiieats #onogrinds #hawaiireels #travelreels

I love getting creative when making dresses for attending weddings! With the different types of dress codes, there’s such a wide variety of outfits to make. I fell in love with @jaclynsalem ‘s recent #m8252 dresses and wanted to try it out for myself! 
-
I made a wearable toile first which I’ll share in a future post, but basically I did view B with a few modifications. I sized down in the bodice, and with the sleeves I cut the biggest size and extended the hem about 3 cm in order to add an elastic and a tiiiny amount of volume. I also made the leg slit a few cm higher too. For the O ring, I used a clear acrylic ring 3 inches in diameter from Amazon. Highly recommend this pattern and will definitely be making a few more in the future!
-
Fabric is rayon from @blackbirdfabrics - I loved how the fabric flowed and it was really easy to work with. 
-
Overall I’m super super happy with how this dress turned out! I made a matching tie for my date ☺️

OB/GYN Residency ✅👩🏽‍🎓: everything everywhere all at once 💫

It’s been a little over a week since my last shift as a resident. These last four years of training have been a wild ride, and I couldn’t have done it without all the friends, family, co-residents, and faculty cheering me on along the way. I’ve experienced some of my life’s lowest lows and highest highs, and it’s hard to believe how much has changed in four years. Thousands of babies delivered, surgeries done, and days/nights in the hospital later, we made it! I take my board exams at the end of July, and will be starting my first real big girl job this fall with UT here in Houston 🥳 send all your friends and family my way!

When I’m pressed for time, i usually make a pattern that I know I like so there won’t be issues with fitting or with the assembly. I chose one of my favorites, the indigo dress from @tillybuttons ! Super easy, soft and chewy, matcha chocolate chip cookies 🍪 🍵 

One stick butter (room temp)
3/4 cup light brown sugar
One egg
1 tsp vanilla extract
11/4 cup all purpose flour
1/2 tsp baking soda
2 tbsp matcha
1/8 tsp salt
1/2 cup white choc chips

- preheat oven to 350 F
- cream butter and sugar
- combine with other wet ingredients
- add dry ingredients
- fold in choc chips
- roll into balls, evenly spaced on baking sheet
- bake 10-12 min until edges golden brown

super proud of these lil throw pillows! I hate getting rid of scraps and I desperately needed new pillow covers so I went with making these!

I used 2.5” strips and used  basic log cabin quilting technique! I bound the pillows using 2.5” strips as well. Quilting is tedious but the final product is always amazing!! I did an envelope binding for the back instead of buttons or zip just for ease. I used a preexisting pillow form to stuff them :) let me know if y’all have any questions or want to make your own! 

All fabric from @riflepaperco

I had so much fun playing with my Cricut Maker to make an appliqué throw pillow! I used leftover heart fabric from Valentine’s Day, applied heat n bond to the back, made the design in Cricut Design space, then cut it out! I used a cotton twill for my main pillow fabric. I then ironed on the letters and reinforced with a zig zag stitch. I finished off the pillow with an overlapping envelope backing and used leftover pink heart fabric for binding, similar to a quilt finish binding! 

The cricut maker was super easy to use to cut the fabric and it cut SO accurately too ✂️ I will definitely get plenty of use out of the fabric cutting function. Please send me your favorite cricut DIYs, especially for sewing! I’d love to try! 

Fabric from @joann_stores

in my ✨linen matching set era✨

I just finished this set and ran to the mirror to take a pic 📸 I’ve had this linen in my stash for months now!!! And I’ve been too scared to cut into it - but for whatever reason, last night and today I decided to make two patterns i had never made before with this precious fabric and I feel like it worked out 🙃 ps does anyone else also rarely wear jeans anymore? Just me? 🙋🏻‍♀️

Top is the new #truebiasaster from @truebias 
- y’all. I have to give major props to this pattern because the details are *chefs kiss* 🤌🏼 the mitered corners, the perfect angles at the straps. It’s a seemingly simple pattern with beautiful and thoughtful details. I’m a huge fan and I can’t wait to make the dress version. 

Pants are the Florence pants from Elizabeth Suzann studio! I made the “short” version but may go for a regular length next time but suffice to say… i am a fan. It’s a simple, no frills pattern that I will probably make 10 versions of 😍 the only change was reducing the hem to 1 cm because when I tried them on, they were a teeny bit too short for my taste. #esmadebyme #esflorencepants @elizsuzann 

Lastly, this amazing fabric is printed linen from @blackbirdfabrics and it is SO good. I have nothing but praise for this fabric. It’s very comfy, breezy, and so easy to work with. The sews like a dream, truly. I can’t wait to see what this linen does as I wash and wear this outfit over time. 

Anyways, thanks for reading this stream of consciousness post. ♥️ 

#blackbirdfabrics #bfprints #htxblogger
